

VtGet(1vtcl)                                         VtGet(1vtcl)

SSyynnooppssiiss
       VtGet widgetName [option]
       VtGetValues widgetName [option]

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       Returns  the  value  of the specified option for the given
       widget.  Only options which have a "G" next to the  option
       name in the command reference can be retrieved with VtGet.
       VtGet can retrieve multiple options from a  single  widget
       in  a  single  command.   The options are retrieved in the
       order in which they appear on the command line.

   OOppttiioonnss
       Any valid options for the particular widget.  For example,
       to  return  the  label string for the widget $myLabel: set
       label [VtGet $myLabel -label] You can specify one  of  the
       dialog  options  -apply,  -cancel, -help,-ok, or -reset to
       retrieve the widget name  of  the  corresponding  built-in
       button  on a form.  For example, to get the widget name of
       the Help button on the form $myForm: set helpbutton [VtGet
       $myForm -help]

RReettuurrnn vvaalluueess
       If VtGet fails, it returns one of the following error mes-
       sages: the option is not gettable  too  many  or  too  few
       options specified See

